      <div xml:id="NA379-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu tōḻi talaimakaṟkut talaimakaḷai maṭamai kūṟiyatu.
          2. kāppuk kaimikak kālattut talaimakaḷ tōḻikkuc colliyatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what the confidante said to HIM about the innocence of HER. 2. It is also what SHE said to the confidante in the time when there was an increase in guards.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA379">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>          puṉṟalai mantik kallā vaṉpaṟaḻ</l>
<l>          kuṉṟuḻai naṇṇiya muṉṟiṟ pōkā</l>
<l>          teriyakain taṉṉa vītatai yiṇara</l>
<l>          vēṅkaiyam paṭuciṉaip poruntik kaiya</l>
<l>          tēmpey tīmpāl vauvaliṟ koṭicci</l>
<l>          yeḻuteḻil citaiya vaḻuta kaṇṇē</l>
<l>          tērvaṇ cōḻar kuṭantai vāyiṉ</l>
<l>          māriyaṅ kiṭaṅki ṉīriya malarnta</l>
<l>          peyaluṟu nīlam pōṉṟaṉa viralē</l>
<l>          pāa yavvayi ṟalaittali ṉāṉā</l>
<l>          tāṭumaḻai tavaḻuṅ kōṭuyar potiyi</l>
<l>          ṉōṅkiruñ cilampiṟ pūtta</l>
<l>          kāntaḷaṅ koḻumukai pōṉṟaṉa civantē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent4">          The eyes</l>
<l>	that cried, for [their] painted grace to be spoiled,</l>
<l rend="indent">	of the creeper woman, when the sweet milk with honey was snatched</l>
<l rend="indent2">	by the untaught strong young one of the red-headed she-monkey</l>
<l rend="indent2">	from [her] hands, not going from the front yard situated near the hills,</l>
<l rend="indent3">	joining the low(?) branches of the Vēṅkai tree</l>
<l rend="indent3">	with clusters full of blossoms as if burning with flames,</l>
<l rend="indent3">– they were like blue lotuses subjected to the rain</l>
<l rend="indent">	that blossomed while the pretty ditches became wet in the shower</l>
<l rend="indent2">	near Kuṭantai of the Cōḻas generous with chariots.</l>
<l rend="indent4">	The fingers,</l>
<l rend="indent">	spreading [and] unendingly slapping [her] belly,</l>
<l rend="indent4">	turning red</l>
<l>they were like the rich buds of the Malabar lily</l>
<l rend="indent">	that flowered on the high dark mountain side</l>
<l rend="indent2">	of Potiyil high with peaks that are covered by playing rain.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
